node.text:
Pretty sure this is the first Apparel Co x Venture Capital collab in history. Definitely won't be our last. @776fund is proud to be working with @RowingBlazers to make our 1st merch drop EXCLUSIVELY for college athletes & in support of their mental health (thx to AAAD). All credit to @jackcarlson and his team for the awesome job on this super limited design.

We've already started putting dollars into supporting our founders via our 2% Growth & Caregiving Program—it's something I know I wish I had when I was a first-time CEO at 22 + clueless about how my mental health affected my output. 

Selected athletes will receive a special edition tee not available to the general public; a RB discount code they can share to raise money for AAAD; + opportunities for additional products + partial scholarships.

Not sure if you all on IG will wanna watch me demo software, but we just added the ability to Give Flowers (Give Thanks) within Cerebro. Because it's really important to know who your allies are + find ways to do right by em. 💐💐💐

Imagine the social graph we will have in a decade when we know all the kindness that's been extended / received in our network. Take it from the guy who coined "Karma" on Reddit -- this is going to be very valuable for ‪7️⃣7️⃣6️⃣‬ and our founders. ‪#BuildInPublic‬

Yes, Venture Capitalists can believe in Karma.
